%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': {'primaryColor': '#4A90D9', 'primaryTextColor': '#ffffff', 'primaryBorderColor': '#2C6FAC', 'lineColor': '#1a1a1a', 'secondaryColor': '#f0f4f8', 'tertiaryColor': '#e8f4f8', 'signalColor': '#1a1a1a', 'signalTextColor': '#1a1a1a', 'activationBkgColor': '#d4e9f7'}}}%%
%% AR Email Management — UI-Triggered Email Processing via Delegated MCP
%% Path C: Serrala/Alevate UI triggers on-demand email processing
%%   1. User selects email in UI
%%   2. UI acquires Microsoft Entra delegated token (MSAL.js PKCE)
%%   3. UI calls CodeMie Assistants API with X-PingOne-Token + X-Graph-Token
%%   4. LangGraph ReAct assistant invokes Outlook MCP tool
%%   5. MCP-Connect Bridge relays X-Graph-Token to Outlook MCP Server
%%   6. Outlook MCP Server fetches email via Graph API (delegated token)
%%   7. Pipeline continues (same agents as webhook path)
%%
%% Compare with: ar-mail-flow-approval-ui.mermaid (webhook push path)
%% Related ADRs: ADR-006 (this pattern), Multi-Tenancy ADR-012 (X-PingOne-Token template)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as AR Specialist<br/>(browser)
    participant UI as Serrala / Alevate UI<br/>(React SPA + MSAL.js)
    participant Entra as Microsoft Entra ID<br/>(Graph OAuth2)
    participant Gate1 as Traefik + oauth2-proxy<br/>(Gate 1)
    participant CM as CodeMie Assistants API<br/>(LangGraph ReAct)
    participant Bridge as MCP-Connect Bridge
    participant OutlookMCP as Outlook MCP Server
    participant Graph as Microsoft Graph API
    participant Audit as Audit Store<br/>(PostgreSQL)
    participant Classifier as EmailClassifier<br/>(A2A agent)

    Note over User,UI: Step 0 — PingOne session already established (Path A, existing)
    Note over UI: UI has PingOne JWT in session<br/>(Authorization + X-PingOne-Token)

    rect rgb(232, 244, 248)
        Note over User,Entra: Step 1 — Microsoft Graph Consent (lazy, on user action)
        User->>UI: Selects email → "Process with AI"
        UI->>Entra: Authorization Request (Auth Code + PKCE)<br/>scope=Mail.Read offline_access
        Entra->>User: Microsoft consent / login prompt<br/>(if not already consented)
        User->>Entra: User consents
        Entra-->>UI: Authorization code
        UI->>Entra: Token exchange (code + PKCE verifier)
        Entra-->>UI: Entra access token (~1h TTL)<br/>+ refresh token
        Note over UI: Graph token stored in memory only<br/>(MSAL.js cache, NOT localStorage)
    end

    rect rgb(232, 248, 232)
        Note over UI,CM: Step 2 — CodeMie Assistants API Call (Path C)
        UI->>Gate1: POST /v1/assistants/{id}/chat<br/>Authorization: Bearer [pingone-jwt]<br/>X-PingOne-Token: [pingone-jwt]<br/>X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token]<br/>{"message": "Process email msg-abc123", "propagate_headers": true}
        Note over Gate1: Gate 1 validates PingOne JWT (RS256, aud, exp)<br/>X-Graph-Token: NOT on MCP_BLOCKED_HEADERS → passes through<br/>Injects X-Tenant-Id, X-User-Id from PingOne JWT claims (for CodeMie multi-tenancy)
        Gate1->>CM: Forward request (all headers intact)
    end

    rect rgb(248, 240, 232)
        Note over CM,Graph: Step 3 — Outlook MCP Tool Invocation
        Note over CM: LangGraph ReAct engine processes request<br/>Decides to invoke get_email MCP tool
        CM->>Bridge: tool_call("get_email", {message_id: "msg-abc123"})<br/>+ request_headers: {X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token],<br/>X-PingOne-Token: [pingone-jwt]}
        Note over Bridge: propagate_headers=true<br/>X-Graph-Token: NOT in MCP_BLOCKED_HEADERS → forwarded<br/>(follows same mechanism as X-PingOne-Token per ADR-012)<br/>X-Tenant-Id / X-User-Id: NOT forwarded to Outlook MCP —<br/>tenant+user identity already embedded in X-Graph-Token JWT claims (tid, sub/oid)
        Bridge->>OutlookMCP: MCP invoke get_email<br/>X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token]
        Note over OutlookMCP: 1. Read X-Graph-Token header (only header needed)<br/>2. Decode JWT — tid = tenant, sub/oid = user identity<br/>3. Check exp claim for token expiry<br/>4. Set Authorization: Bearer [entra-access-token]<br/>5. Call Graph API
        OutlookMCP->>Graph: GET /me/messages/msg-abc123<br/>Authorization: Bearer [entra-access-token]<br/>Accept: application/json<br/>(+ ConsistencyLevel: eventual — only for search_emails KQL $search)
        Graph-->>OutlookMCP: Email content + metadata + thread refs
        Note over OutlookMCP: ADR-007 optional Presidio before MCP sampling PII_RESPONSE_LEVEL shapes tool JSON
        OutlookMCP-->>Bridge: MCP tool result email object per response level
        Bridge-->>CM: Email content in assistant context
    end

    rect rgb(248, 232, 248)
        Note over CM,Audit: Step 4 — Pipeline Processing (same as webhook path)
        CM->>Audit: Log: trigger_source=ui_pull, message_id=msg-abc123,<br/>user_id=[user-sub], tenant_id=[tenant-id]
        CM->>Classifier: A2A: classify email<br/>(email content + thread context from MCP tool result)
        Classifier-->>CM: {category, confidence, intent, reasoning}
        CM->>Audit: Log classification: category, confidence, reasoning
        Note over CM: Pipeline continues via A2A:<br/>ThreadSummarizer → ResponseDrafter<br/>→ ActionRouter → ReviewPresenter
        Note over CM: Workflow enters PAUSED state<br/>awaiting human approval
        CM->>Audit: Log: review_package_hash, target_ui=Alevate
    end

    Note over CM,User: Step 5 — Human Approval (same as webhook path)<br/>See ar-mail-flow-approval-ui.mermaid for approval sequence

    rect rgb(252, 244, 220)
        Note over CM,Entra: Alt: Graph Token Expired During Processing
        alt Entra access token expired
            OutlookMCP->>OutlookMCP: exp < now() → token expired
            OutlookMCP-->>Bridge: HTTP 401 {error: "token_expired",<br/>code: "ERR_GRAPH_TOKEN_EXPIRED",<br/>message: "Entra access token expired. Obtain fresh token and retry."}
            Bridge-->>CM: Tool error: ERR_GRAPH_TOKEN_EXPIRED
            CM-->>Gate1: HTTP 401 {code: ERR_GRAPH_TOKEN_EXPIRED}
            Gate1-->>UI: HTTP 401
            UI->>Entra: msal.acquireTokenSilent({scopes: ["Mail.Read"]})
            Entra-->>UI: Fresh Entra access token
            Note over UI: Retry with fresh X-Graph-Token
            UI->>Gate1: Retry POST /v1/assistants/{id}/chat<br/>X-Graph-Token: [fresh-entra-token]
        end
    end
